cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.DS, cs.GR 

The paper deals with image processing techniques for automatic identification of fission tracks in mineral photomicrographs. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR) as the paper deals with image segmentation and feature extraction. The use of wavelets for image processing also suggests the possibility of multimedia (cs.MM) being a relevant sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves evaluation of results using precision, recall and accuracy, which are common metrics in data science (cs.DS). Finally, the use of algorithms for image processing and analysis suggests that graphics (cs.GR) could also be a relevant sub-category.
